N_{H}=\left(\frac{L}{L+L^{*}}\right)\frac{1}{\gamma}\left[\sqrt{\frac{(L+L^{*})\beta}{S}}[\alpha-\sigma]-2\beta\right]
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
N_{H}=\frac{L}{\gamma}\sqrt{\frac{\beta}{(L+L^{*})S}}[\alpha-\sigma]-\left(\frac{L}{L+L^{*}}\right)\frac{1}{\gamma}2\beta
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Returns to scale?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If 
\begin_inset Formula $L+L^{*}=\phi L$
\end_inset

, (and 
\begin_inset Formula $\phi>1$
\end_inset

) then 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
N_{H}=\frac{1}{\phi}\frac{1}{\gamma}\left[\sqrt{\frac{\phi L\beta}{S}}[\alpha-\sigma]-2\beta\right]
\]

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\[
N_{H}=\frac{1}{\gamma}\left[\frac{\sqrt{\phi}}{\phi}\sqrt{\frac{L\beta}{S}}[\alpha-\sigma]-\frac{2\beta}{\phi}\right]
\]

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\[
N_{H}-N_{old}=\frac{1}{\gamma}\left[\frac{\sqrt{\phi}}{\phi}\sqrt{\frac{L\beta}{S}}[\alpha-\sigma]-\frac{2\beta}{\phi}-\sqrt{\frac{L\beta}{S}}[\alpha-\sigma]+2\beta\right]
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
=\frac{1}{\gamma}\left[\left(\frac{\sqrt{\phi}}{\phi}-1\right)\sqrt{\frac{L\beta}{S}}[\alpha-\sigma]+\left(1-\frac{1}{\phi}\right)2\beta\right]
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
As 
\begin_inset Formula $\phi\to\infty$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
=\frac{1}{\gamma}\left[2\beta-\sqrt{\frac{L\beta}{S}}[\alpha-\sigma]\right]
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If we set to zero and solve for 
\begin_inset Formula $L$
\end_inset

, we can find the smallest initial population that can't have more local
 varieties when opening to trade, even if partner if infinitely large.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\frac{4\beta S}{[\alpha-\sigma]^{2}}=L
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And to find the L where you have zero varieties in the first place, wait
 is it the same?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
N_{old}=\frac{1}{\phi}\frac{1}{\gamma}\left[\sqrt{\frac{\phi L\beta}{S}}[\alpha-\sigma]-2\beta\right]
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For example, beta = 1 >>> S = 1 >>> alpha = 2 >>> sigma = 1 >>> L = 9 >>>
 Lstar = 9 >>> gamma = 1 makes both increase.
 Chane Lstar to 16, and only one increases.
 Change both to 16 and both decrease instead
\end_layout

